              I only do a whole boil, I've never split my batches and run different temps. kinda sorta <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/wink.png" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> mostly because I dont use 3 containers, I use two, so my sparge water stays in my keggle and when its temp drops I'll heat it back up, so my sparge will often be a 'range' of temp, but nothing drastic.

              

              
              
            </div>
