        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">Pocky Is God wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Pysgard wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">++ rrrhal.<br /><br />Batch sparge is faster, but more work. I've taken to fly sparging, although my mash tun was not suited to it, I was still getting 70%. I'll be rebuilding with a proper false bottom soon.</div><br /><br /><br />Yeah, the fly sparge seems like its easier, but it takes longer. So assuming I buy the kit linked or make my own, what temp do you guys use when you fly sparge and how long does it take?</div><br />Ideally fly sparging lasts ~30 minutes.  Ideally the water coming in (the sparge liquor) is ~176 degrees.  I basically boil my sparge liquor, turn off the heat, and let it stop bubbling.  Then dump it all into my sparge bucket.  Put the lid on (loosly), wrap the bucket with a fleece and some towels and start the flow.  Recirculate about a quart or two of wort (or not) and collect the rest and boil it.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
