          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Back to Sparge techniques:<br /><br />Please tell me if I'm doing this wrong:  I typically mash about 7 gallons of water and prepare 5 more gallons at 170degrees that I stash in a gatorade cooler. After my 60-minute mash, I take my first runnings into the boil pot, mix in half the sparge water, stir it up, let sit for 10 minutes, drain into boil pot, repeat with last half.  This nets about 9 gallons that I boil down for 90 minutes.<br /><br />What I'm NOT doing is adding sparge water prior to the first runnings from mash tun, which is what it sounded like rrhal was suggesting.<br /><br />This last weekend I knew I wasn't going to be able to batch sparge so I added 30% to the grain bill and mashed with 10 gallons.  That grain soaked up a lot more water than expected and I only got about 5 gallons from the mash tun to which I added about 3.5 for the boil.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
