              After a brewing hiatus, I'm going to whip up a batch of apfelwien this weekend. BONUS: I'll finally have a chance to try out the chest freezer I got for Christmas for keeping stable fermentation temps.<br /><br />The current iteration of the recipe is:<br /><br />-5 gal 100% apple juice<br />-5 lbs turbinado sugar<br />-2 pkgs Nottingham dry yeast<br />-2 yeast nutrient<br />-1 12 oz container cranberry apple juice concentrate (priming)<br /><br />The previous batches I've made have always fermented in a water bath in a closet, so the temps have always varied. I'm going to keep this batch at about 65F this time around for a month before bottling, and give the bottles about 2 months to age before opening, meaning I'll have plenty of refreshing booze for the brutal AZ summer.<br /><br />My next version, I'm planning on reducing 6 gallons of apple juice down to 5 and dialing the turbinado back to about 3 lbs. I'd try this recipe now, but it's already approaching the &quot;too hot for brewing&quot; weather here in Phoenix.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
