              Wow .. so I came to the conclusion yesterday that bottling blows and I'm going to start putting together a basic kegging setup sooner than later.  I bottled one batch (48 bottles) and between soaking the bottles, removing the labels, rinsing, and sanitizing, filling and capping, it was literally an all day event.. and only half the bottles needed the labels removed.  Ugh.  But the sample I tasted out of the hydrometer tasted good prior to adding the cherry extract, so I have high hopes for the beer.  Brewed again today, a very simple American Amber Ale.. extract with some steeping grains, 1oz cascade hops, 1oz Mount Hood.  Should ferment out quick and be ready soon... hoping 2-3 weeks.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
